  "title": "hierarchicalMenu widget sorts by isRefined if provided with sortBy compareFunction",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nBug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\nTake a look at the two hirarchicalMenu Widgets I've created: \r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/jv145lmzn9\r\n\r\nI've created a default one, and one with a sortBy function applied.\r\nNotice that by default isRefined is not on. \r\nOnce a sortBy function is provided, isRefined is on.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\nThat the defaults for the widget remains consistent. If isRefined is not the default\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nAll browsers.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\nHave the widget remain isRefined=false in either case.\r\nAdditionally, provide way to refine if you want isRefined on or not in conjunction with a sortBy Function.\r\nI've created this feature request regarding this: #2810\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\nTested only on 2.x+ \r\n",
